{
  "texts": [
    "Without any lensing mass, the frozen wavefront is simply a plane, and the time taken for backward wavefront to reach it follows from geometry as The wavefront proceeds as the dotted curves and is then frozen at the solid black curve.",
    "Then a second backward wavefront (dashed) emerges from the observer on the ground.",
    "Each of the dashed curves is the endpoint at a particular time of rays emanating from the observer, but those rays are not shown where D is the shortest distance from the observer to the frozen wavefront.",
    "Since β is constant, we can equivalently write",
    "Adding a lensing mass, the frozen wavefront gets warped, and the time taken by the backward wavefront to reach it changes by say t grav (θ)."
  ]
}